{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17659580","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17659580"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T23:11:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T23:11:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20872"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20872","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20872"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13747"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97627"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13747","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13747"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20872"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80227"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"8133"},{"type":"tags","id":"11595"},{"type":"tags","id":"12325"},{"type":"tags","id":"12694"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"33083"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33084"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97627","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/97627"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman is diagnosed with HIV infection. Her healthcare team is considering antiretroviral therapy that includes abacavir.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tests must be performed before initiating abacavir therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["HLA-A*3101 genetic test","HLA-B*5701 genetic test","HLA-B*1502 genetic test","HLA-B*5801 genetic test","HLA-DRB1*0701 genetic test"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-B*5701 genetic test\u003C/strong\u003E must be performed before starting abacavir therapy. Patients who carry this genetic variant are at high risk of developing severe hypersensitivity reactions to abacavir. A positive test is an absolute contraindication to abacavir use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent other HLA alleles associated with different drug reactions:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-A*3101\u003C/strong\u003E - Associated with carbamazepine hypersensitivity in European populations\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-B*1502\u003C/strong\u003E - Associated with Stevens-Johnson syndrome from carbamazepine in Asian populations\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-B*5801\u003C/strong\u003E - Associated with severe cutaneous adverse reactions to allopurinol\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHLA-DRB1*0701\u003C/strong\u003E - Associated with liver injury from ximelagatran\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHLA-B*5701 screening has become standard practice before abacavir use, as it has significantly reduced the incidence of potentially life-threatening hypersensitivity reactions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["HLA-B*5701 testing must be performed before starting abacavir to prevent severe hypersensitivity reactions.","A positive HLA-B*5701 result is an absolute contraindication to abacavir use.","Different HLA alleles are associated with distinct drug hypersensitivity reactions."],"references":["Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC. Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020. Chapter 6; pages 253-255."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80227"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20872"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"80227","links":{"self":"https: